resources.string: Please make sure you have read and understood the DJI AirSense Warnings.

Aircraft in flight. Unable to switch remote controller status
Imperial unit mode set successfully. Measurement values will now follow imperial unit system. Since the aircraft supports metric unit system, the values seen are approximate conversions.
Are you sure you want to format the internal storage (eMMC)?
The aircraft will automatically retract the landing gear and enter Travel Mode.
The map has not been initialized yet

By tapping Unlock, you agree that you have the authorization to operate in this fly zone. A record of this request will be linked to your DJI account. Tap Cancel to abort the operation.
Failed to unlock. You are not authorized to unlock this zone.
Aircraft is hovering low. Ensure the landing point is safe and push the stick downward to land.
Aircraft will land at its current location. Check landing area is clear.

Failed to set. Input number in range.
Map Loading failed , depend Map lib not found!
Another aircraft is dangerously close, please descend to a safer altitude.
Another aircraft is too close, please descend to a safer altitude.
Another aircraft is nearby. Fly with caution.
Flight speed and sensitivity will be substantially increased when you turn off Beginner mode. Fly with caution.
Beginner mode enabled. Altitude and distance will both be limited to 100ft / 30m.

With Precision Takeoff Mode enabled, the aircraft will automatically ascend to %1$s. This allows the aircraft to return to home point more accurately with VPS images. Ensure there is sufficient ambient light and that the takeoff route isn\'t blocked by trees, power lines or other objects. Moving the sticks during takeoff may affect image acquisition. In an emergency, use the control sticks to throttle downward.
Connection error, please check that the authorization code is correct.
Current controller already has gimbal control.
Current controller already has gimbal control.
Authorization code not entered, please enter again.
Remote controller name must be less than 6 characters in length.
Aircraft flight control locked by companion controller. Current RC does not have permissions for modifying low battery settings
Aircraft flight control locked by companion controller. Unable to modify settings
Aircraft flight control locked companion controller. Current RC does not have permissions for modifying flight controller settings
Please turn on gimbal control in remote controller settings.
Aircraft flight control locked by companion controller. Current RC does not have permissions for modifying obstacle avoidance settings.
Aircraft flight control locked by companion controller. Current RC does not have permissions for modifying RTK settings
Password must be 4 digits in length.
Failed to set, please try again.
The distance between the aircraft and Home Point is less than 65.6 ft (20 m). The aircraft will return home at its current altitude if RTH is initiated.

Aircraft will adjust its nose direction to face the home point, and its altitude to %1$s. Current aircraft altitude is %2$s. Press Return to Home button directly on your remote to cancel this procedure, or take over control sticks.
The aircraft is less than 20 m (65.6 ft) from the Home Point. The aircraft will land if Return to Home is initiated.
Approaching a No-Fly Zone. Current RTH route may be distorted. Monitor the aircraft\'s flight path on the map or visually to ensure safety.
Aircraft will head to home point and set RTH route. Use virtual joystick to adjust flight direction. Tap Cancel RTH button to stop RTH.
Return to home altitude cannot exceed maximum flight altitude %1$d.
The return altitude has been changed, please pay attention to flight safety.
Make sure D-RTK 2 Mobile Station is in open area and do not adjust position after setup. Unable to connect to mobile station after starting aircraft propellers

1. Check whether the D-RTK 2 Mobile Station is powered on\n2. Ensure the D-RTK 2 Mobile Station is placed in an open area free of obstructions\n3. Check whether the D-RTK 2 Mobile Station is set in Broadcast mode
Request failed. Check and try again
Custom network RTK not supported by Controller B
Network RTK not supported by Controller B
When RTK module malfunctions, manually disable RTK and switch back to GPS mode. (If you enable RTK after takeoff, the GPS will continually be used.)
Motors are running. Stop them and try again.
Broadcast mode is indicated by the indicator blinking five times in a row
Press and hold the linking button for 3 seconds while pressing the M button simultaneously. The indicator will blink red several times to indicate that the password has been reset to 123456
Press and hold the power button for 3 seconds. The indicator will display solid green to indicate initialization is complete
Press and hold the operating mode button for two seconds until the indicator blinks yellow. Then, press the same button to switch mobile station modes.
The device automatically restarts after switching to and from Broadcast mode. Restarting takes around 10s
Go to RTK Settings and select the current D-RTK 2 mobile station. Linking is now complete

Real-Time Kinematic positioning is based on the phase of the signal\'s carrier phase and outputs centimeter-level 3D positioning on particular coordinates. Heading is determined by the two antennas of the rover.

In case of an RTK module communication error, the aircraft will automatically maintain the current RTK status with gradually decreasing accuracy. The aircraft will exit RTK if the connection is not re-established within 10 minutes.
Make sure D-RTK 2 Mobile Station is in open area and do not adjust position after setup. Unable to connect to mobile station after starting aircraft propellers
Motors are running. Stop them and try again.
RTK service error. Restart DJI Pilot or aircraft and try again
Receiving RTK signal. Ensure network connection is stable
Restart aircraft after switching RTK services
RTK connected. RTK data in use
RTK connected. RTK data not in use

Unable to switch VI or multi spectral lens in current shooting mode

Ensure that conditions are safe for takeoff. Aircraft will go to an altitude of %1$s and hover.

The aircraft will enter Travel Mode for easier transportation. Place the aircraft on a flat, hard surface and remove the gimbal. If the aircraft does not enter Travel Mode, adjust the landing gear manually.
Area is not suitable for landing. Please move to a safer location.
Logged in but not authorized to unlock flyzones.
Obstacle Avoidance Disabled. Fly with caution.
